Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.61,0:01:35.28,Yaku M,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Entering the Capital Freeway.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.28,0:01:37.51,Yaku M,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}No delays yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.51,0:01:39.66,Yaku M,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}We should arrive at Fukui in five hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.06,0:01:49.04,Yaku M,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Hey, aren't you loading a little too much?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.40,0:01:51.61,Yaku M,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Keep your distance just in case.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.61,0:01:52.50,Yaku M,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.20,0:02:05.10,Yaku M,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}That bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.10,0:02:05.98,Yaku M,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.98,0:02:08.07,Yaku M,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}We have to get out of here first.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.74,0:02:30.81,Yaku T,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}My name is Izumida Jun'ichirou.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.81,0:02:33.00,Yaku T,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}I am Yakushiji Ryoko's butler...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.00,0:02:34.63,Yaku T,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}or so it seems.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.20,0:02:41.69,Yaku T,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}For some odd reason, it seems my master loves to get involved in my private affairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.69,0:02:45.64,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Umm, Superintendent, do you actually have something to tell me?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.64,0:02:47.86,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}You're misunderstanding something.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.86,0:02:52.37,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}I just happened to come and it was just coincidental that I sat here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.37,0:02:57.19,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}And it'll be terrible if something happens...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.19,0:02:59.22,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Meeting with a grade schooler here at a time like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.22,0:03:01.66,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Nothing will happen at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.16,0:03:05.08,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Besides, I've already told you that Mana-chan is my cousin.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.08,0:03:07.62,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Even if she's your cousin, it's still a crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.26,0:03:12.63,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Say, Mana-chan, why don't you tell me?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.20,0:03:20.36,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Your mom was really worried that you might be bullied at school.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.36,0:03:24.50,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}You promised your mom that you'd tell me, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.54,0:03:28.03,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}She doesn't want to tell you.  Why don't you leave her alone?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.03,0:03:28.72,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Superintendent!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.16,0:03:32.33,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Being bullied isn't that simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.33,0:03:37.61,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Even though you say that, you actually just want to talk to grade school girls, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.61,0:03:38.73,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.73,0:03:41.76,Yaku M,Man,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Jun-chan, you were the one who broke our promise first!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.01,0:03:44.24,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Jun-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.39,0:03:46.77,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.77,0:03:51.00,Yaku M,Man,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}I told her that I would tell you if we were alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.23,0:03:53.96,Yaku M,Man,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Why did you bring this woman with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.36,0:03:59.17,Yaku T,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}"Bring" and "tagged along" are two totally different things, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.17,0:04:00.17,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.17,0:04:02.77,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}I apologize for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.77,0:04:05.43,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}So would you please tell me the truth?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.88,0:04:07.93,Yaku M,Man,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.20,0:04:09.81,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Great.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.81,0:04:13.55,Yaku M,Man,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}I'm not actually being bullied.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.55,0:04:18.27,Yaku M,Man,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}I had a fight with a friend and my mom just overreacted.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.37,0:04:20.23,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.54,0:04:26.07,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Then you should have said so in the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.55,0:04:30.46,Yaku M,Man,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}But you'd leave right away if I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.43,0:04:34.55,Yaku M,Man,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Say, Jun-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.55,0:04:37.08,Yaku M,Man,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Who is she?  She has nothing to do with this. 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.08,0:04:39.43,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}How rude!  I am involved with this.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.43,0:04:41.63,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}I'm Izumida-kun's ruler.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.63,0:04:42.46,Yaku M,Man,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Ruler?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.46,0:04:45.09,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}She's my boss, Superintendent Yakushiji.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.09,0:04:45.80,Yaku M,Man,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Superintendent?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.22,0:04:48.66,Yaku M,Man,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Superintendents are really powerful people, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.66,0:04:50.76,Yaku M,Man,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Isn't she younger than you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.01,0:04:53.52,Yaku M,Man,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Or is she unexpectedly old?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.52,0:04:54.27,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Old?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.68,0:04:56.59,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}It's called a career bureaucrat.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.59,0:04:57.70,Yaku M,Man,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Career?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.70,0:04:58.80,Yaku M,Man,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Oh, I know about them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.80,0:05:02.53,Yaku M,Man,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}They're people who don't do much work but they boss others around.  They're egocentric.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.15,0:05:08.45,Yaku T,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}I believe most career bureaucrats are great people who shoulder Japan's future.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.45,0:05:15.33,Yaku T,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}However, in regards to Yakushiji Ryoko, her egocentricity is definitely on the mark.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.33,0:05:18.70,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Well then, the case is closed, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.70,0:05:20.66,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Kids should go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.66,0:05:21.80,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}She's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.80,0:05:23.26,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}It's already very late.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.70,0:05:25.77,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Mana-chan, I'll take you home.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.38,0:05:33.08,Yaku M,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}As ordered, we're at Aoyama Broadway.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.67,0:05:34.41,Yaku M,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.94,0:05:35.99,Yaku M,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.61,0:05:40.69,Yaku M,Sec,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Transporters, I don't think you can make it to Fukui after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.69,0:05:43.32,Yaku M,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Another truck will be here soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.32,0:05:45.31,Yaku M,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}We'd like to transfer the material.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.31,0:05:47.55,Yaku M,Sec,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}The door's bent.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.55,0:05:49.87,Yaku M,Sec,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}I think it'll be faster if we dismantle it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.87,0:05:51.16,Yaku M,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}I'll leave that to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.69,0:05:52.67,Yaku M,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Please hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.67,0:05:54.66,Yaku M,Sec,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Yeah, we'll start right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.68,0:06:00.42,Yaku M,Sec,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}They brought the truck to a building we guard just to transfer the material.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.75,0:06:03.73,Yaku M,Sec,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}It must be something they really don't want anyone to know about.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.57,0:06:27.88,Yaku M,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Lower the shutters in the front!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.88,0:06:28.99,Yaku M,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Don't let that thing out!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.62,0:06:48.36,Yaku M,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}It started to move.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.36,0:06:50.04,Yaku M,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}We can't do anything about it alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.04,0:06:51.76,Yaku M,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Please send reinforcements ASAP!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.94,0:06:54.72,Yaku M,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Reinforcements.  Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.80,0:07:08.60,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}But why did you fight with your friends?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.60,0:07:10.79,Yaku M,Man,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}It's because they said stupid things
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.79,0:07:13.42,Yaku M,Man,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}after looking at my photographs without telling me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.42,0:07:14.70,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Photographs?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.70,0:07:15.87,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Photographs of what?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.19,0:07:18.00,Yaku M,Man,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}It's...  I forget.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.00,0:07:20.08,Yaku M,Man,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}They were just your usual photographs.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.87,0:07:26.18,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}I heard gunfire.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.67,0:07:27.64,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}It came from that building!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.64,0:07:28.58,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Superintendent!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.13,0:07:31.09,Yaku M,Man,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Hey, Jun-chan, where are you going?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.48,0:07:34.52,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Superintendent!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.41,0:07:36.84,Yaku M,Jan,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Inside this building?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.35,0:07:38.16,Yaku M,Man,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Jun-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.16,0:07:40.98,Yaku M,Man,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Leaving me back there!  How could you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.98,0:07:42.33,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Oh, I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.33,0:07:45.26,Yaku M,Man,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}This is Aoyama Broadway, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.26,0:07:48.06,Yaku M,Man,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}What do you want?  The store has already closed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.03,0:07:51.32,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Did you really hear gunfire coming from this building?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.05,0:07:57.28,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.66,0:07:59.29,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Can't you tell?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.18,0:08:02.98,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}I'm sorry, Mana-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.98,0:08:05.00,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Can you wait at the store we were at earlier?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.20,0:08:07.04,Yaku M,Man,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}What about you, Jun-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.04,0:08:09.70,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}I can't let her go alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.70,0:08:10.76,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}I'll be going in too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.19,0:08:13.42,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Can you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.42,0:08:15.33,Yaku M,Man,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Of course I can.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.69,0:08:17.44,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Good girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.95,0:08:25.81,Yaku M,Man,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Jun'ichirou, you idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.27,0:08:31.07,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Superintendent, where are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.07,0:08:33.24,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Over here, Izumida-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.63,0:08:35.82,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Really...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.55,0:08:56.80,Yaku M,Man,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Does he think he can just leave me alone?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.54,0:09:07.23,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}They're already dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.13,0:09:09.23,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}All of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.97,0:09:11.47,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}How awful.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.47,0:09:13.69,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}It looks like they've been cut up with a knife.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.69,0:09:16.46,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}A very sharp one at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.46,0:09:20.68,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Huh?  If a knife was the weapon, why was there gunfire?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.68,0:09:22.74,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}It was probably theirs.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.59,0:09:25.83,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}A gun!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.83,0:09:27.96,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Why do they have guns?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.96,0:09:30.31,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}It means that they're not your ordinary transporters.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.30,0:09:34.61,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}This is the uniform of the Japanese Private Police.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.61,0:09:36.77,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}The Japanese Private Police?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.77,0:09:41.51,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}That's the biggest rival of JACES, your father's company.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.50,0:09:44.96,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Things are becoming fishy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.96,0:09:46.68,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.80,0:09:54.42,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}It looks like the one that killed the security guards is still in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.42,0:09:59.00,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}We don't even know who he is.  It's dangerous in this darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.00,0:10:02.22,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Yes, this isn't a fun situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.22,0:10:03.83,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Let's retreat for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.52,0:10:06.25,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}You see the elevator up ahead, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.41,0:10:10.56,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}I understand.  Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.17,0:10:52.00,Yaku M,Man,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Jun-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.24,0:10:55.30,Yaku M,Man,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Jun-chan, where are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.30,0:10:56.26,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Mana!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.22,0:11:01.13,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Don't come, Mana!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.13,0:11:03.05,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Go back!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.33,0:11:05.47,Yaku M,Man,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Jun-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.97,0:11:09.75,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Mana!  Mana!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.75,0:11:12.01,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Calm down, Izumida-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.85,0:11:14.25,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}It's all my fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.25,0:11:16.94,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}I shouldn't have left her alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.77,0:11:24.22,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Wh-What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.22,0:11:25.07,Yaku M,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Don't talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.07,0:11:26.16,Yaku M,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Just get off.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.16,0:11:27.98,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}There's a child down there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.98,0:11:29.82,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}We must go back right away!  She's in danger!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.82,0:11:30.73,Yaku M,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.36,0:11:33.05,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Who the hell are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.05,0:11:34.17,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}I'm with the police!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.65,0:11:40.73,Yaku M,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}We don't want to do anything rough.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.73,0:11:43.01,Yaku M,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}After all, we don't want any more casualties.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.50,0:11:46.01,Yaku M,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Will you obey our orders?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.40,0:12:10.35,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}It's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.35,0:12:11.04,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Listen to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.04,0:12:14.59,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}There's a girl that's still in the underground parking lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.59,0:12:15.76,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}She's ten years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.76,0:12:16.34,Yaku M,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.34,0:12:19.67,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}You guys know what's down there, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.67,0:12:21.79,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Then please go save Mana right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.79,0:12:22.25,Yaku M,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.25,0:12:25.76,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Or else untie me, quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.76,0:12:27.17,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.17,0:12:28.16,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Hey, bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.16,0:12:28.72,Yaku M,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}How is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.44,0:12:30.33,Yaku M,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}We've found it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.33,0:12:33.08,Yaku M,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}But there's a child right beside it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.08,0:12:33.93,Yaku M,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Positive?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.93,0:12:34.88,Yaku M,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Positive.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.88,0:12:36.19,Yaku M,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}It's a girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.04,0:12:44.36,Yaku M,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}It moved.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.36,0:12:45.32,Yaku M,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}The girl's in danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.32,0:12:46.19,Yaku M,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}We'll take her into our protection.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.28,0:12:49.07,Yaku M,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}What should we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.07,0:12:49.89,Yaku M,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}I can't see the girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.89,0:12:52.61,Yaku M,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}We might hit her if we shoot.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.61,0:12:54.24,Yaku M,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}She'll be killed if we don't do anything about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.24,0:12:55.60,Yaku M,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}We must move it away from her.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.60,0:12:56.65,Yaku M,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}But how?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.84,0:12:58.60,Yaku M,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Damn!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.99,0:13:06.51,Yaku M,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.05,0:13:08.19,Yaku T,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.19,0:13:09.18,Yaku T,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Answer me!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.78,0:13:14.52,Yaku M,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}We'll go down now and protect the girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.52,0:13:16.40,Yaku M,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}We are confirming your identities.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.40,0:13:19.90,Yaku M,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}If we find that you're really from the Metropolitan Police Department, we'll release you right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.90,0:13:21.73,Yaku M,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Stay quiet until we do.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.29,0:13:25.38,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}If you use the underground network of the Japan Private Police,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.38,0:13:27.66,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}I doubt the confirmation would even take a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.63,0:13:31.16,Yaku M,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}I don't understand what you're saying.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.16,0:13:35.37,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}You intend to buy more time and erase all the evidence, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.37,0:13:38.29,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}The corpses and that murder machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.22,0:13:42.41,Yaku M,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}I don't know who you are,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.41,0:13:46.26,Yaku M,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}but I think it's best for both of us if you don't stick your nose where it doesn't belong.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.07,0:13:53.78,Yaku M,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Keep an eye on them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.78,0:13:54.83,Yaku M,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Yes, Sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.83,0:13:56.07,Yaku M,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}The rest, come with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.07,0:13:56.89,Yaku M,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Yes, Sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.51,0:14:06.20,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}I'm sure she's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.33,0:14:09.45,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}That's if my assumption is correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.21,0:14:15.20,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Rather, the ones in danger are the Japan Private Police.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.74,0:14:17.44,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}They're a security company.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.44,0:14:20.97,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Yet, they enter wars and replace the military in war-torn regions behind the scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.97,0:14:22.55,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}They're a dark organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.55,0:14:25.63,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}The soldiers are probably from there too.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.09,0:14:28.31,Yaku T,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}We're in the control room.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.31,0:14:31.77,Yaku T,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}We can switch the basement to backup power any time now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.77,0:14:33.45,Yaku M,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Okay, switch it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.45,0:14:34.02,Yaku T,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Roger that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.52,0:14:45.07,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}No, Izumida-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.07,0:14:46.60,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Not here!  No!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.60,0:14:48.61,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Someone save me!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.61,0:14:49.34,Yaku M,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}What's wrong?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.07,0:14:51.25,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}What do you think you're doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.25,0:14:51.86,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}No!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.86,0:14:52.94,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}You can't!  Izumida-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.94,0:14:53.82,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}No!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.82,0:14:56.14,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Pervert!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.14,0:14:58.15,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Superintendent, that's enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.15,0:14:58.67,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.67,0:15:00.06,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Over already?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.06,0:15:01.07,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}How boring.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.07,0:15:02.29,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}We're not playing around.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.72,0:15:06.62,Yaku M,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}We've found it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.62,0:15:08.22,Yaku M,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}It's at the end of the west block, in front of the wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.56,0:15:09.74,Yaku M,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.74,0:15:11.68,Yaku M,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Everyone move to the west block.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.68,0:15:15.83,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}It seems like the machine moved to the west of the parking lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.83,0:15:17.57,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Let's go too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.57,0:15:19.41,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}You should leave the gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.16,0:15:20.65,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}But...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.86,0:15:25.11,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}You have an idea of what the machine is, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.44,0:15:27.53,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.51,0:15:34.11,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}The Japan Private Police were recently given complete control over the protection of nuclear power plants.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.11,0:15:39.41,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}The decisive factor was the completely autonomous security robot they had secretly invented.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.41,0:15:42.92,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Why do you have such intimate knowledge about your rivals?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.92,0:15:44.34,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Of course I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.03,0:15:47.13,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}They probably got into an accident during the transfer or something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.34,0:15:50.22,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}They evacuated it to this building, guarded by the Japan Private Police.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.85,0:15:54.49,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}But the robot malfunctioned due to the shock of the accident and went berserk.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.49,0:15:56.45,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}That's probably what happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.92,0:16:00.76,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}It seems like it has started already.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.67,0:16:10.03,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}That's terrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.03,0:16:13.32,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}That thing wasn't built just for security.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.32,0:16:14.97,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.97,0:16:17.11,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}That isn't just a security robot.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.13,0:16:20.50,Yaku M,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Bastards, why are you here?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.90,0:16:26.08,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}How does it feel to be chased around by the anti-terrorist weapon you invented?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.08,0:16:27.67,Yaku M,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Wh-What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.05,0:16:31.79,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}You armed it so that it would be able to defend against terrorist attacks on a nuclear power plant.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.79,0:16:33.13,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}An anti-terrorist weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.87,0:16:36.01,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}That's what it is, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.01,0:16:39.02,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}But are you saying Japan approved of something like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.02,0:16:40.41,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Of course it's a secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.41,0:16:42.93,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}That's why they're desperately hiding it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.93,0:16:44.30,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}But too bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.30,0:16:48.69,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}I just called them earlier, so it's only a matter of time before the police arrive.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.61,0:16:53.82,Yaku M,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}I warned you about sticking your nose in places where it doesn't belong.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.97,0:17:13.61,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Izumida-kun, you too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.61,0:17:14.33,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.33,0:17:15.51,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Y-Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.95,0:17:21.19,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.19,0:17:25.07,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Even if it malfunctioned, it didn't go completely berserk.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.07,0:17:28.99,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Its ability to distinguish between terrorist and civilian is active.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.99,0:17:32.43,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}It decides that by seeing whether we hold weapons or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.43,0:17:33.95,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}That simple?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.22,0:17:37.95,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}The program was running because it was that simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.46,0:17:40.53,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Remember when we were attacked the first time?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.53,0:17:43.16,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}It didn't attack us until I took out my gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.65,0:17:44.58,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Oh, yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.15,0:17:46.66,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}That's when it hit me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.41,0:17:48.68,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}More importantly, where is she?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.68,0:17:49.38,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Where is Mana?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.38,0:17:56.47,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}That centipede probably has a program to evacuate workers to a safe place when a battle begins.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.06,0:18:05.64,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Mana!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.73,0:18:10.73,Yaku M,Man,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Jun-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.10,0:18:13.14,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.14,0:18:13.78,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Are you hurt anywhere?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.17,0:18:17.41,Yaku M,Man,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.41,0:18:19.87,Yaku M,Man,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}I... I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.87,0:18:23.20,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}No, it's my fault for leaving you alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.63,0:18:24.53,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.56,0:18:27.17,Yaku M,Man,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Jun-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.99,0:18:31.30,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Well then.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.46,0:18:33.50,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.01,0:18:36.71,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}We can't leave that centipede be.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.71,0:18:37.97,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Please stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.97,0:18:39.09,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}It's dangerous!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.29,0:18:41.46,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}I'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.84,0:18:44.20,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Now, centipede,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.20,0:18:46.10,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}come get me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.15,0:18:50.81,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Superintendent!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.10,0:19:05.27,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}It stopped.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.46,0:19:09.00,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}An eye that distinguishes between terrorist and civilian.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.50,0:19:15.45,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}After losing it, it may harm a civilian when it blindly attacks.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.45,0:19:18.97,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}For safety's sake, an emergency shutdown is the only thing it can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.73,0:19:22.47,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}That is also a basic program.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.72,0:19:54.09,Yaku M,Man,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}That robot was trying to protect me, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.58,0:19:57.70,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Yes, I guess it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.55,0:20:01.18,Yaku T,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Why does she have a smile on her face?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.18,0:20:03.01,Yaku T,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}I have a bad feeling about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.63,0:20:08.80,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Now the Japan Private Police won't be able to protect nuclear power plants.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.80,0:20:12.21,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Don't tell me that was your plan from the beginning?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.21,0:20:15.52,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Izumida-kun, the police inspector said he wanted to hear about the situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.80,0:20:17.00,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Go.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.00,0:20:18.88,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}I'll look after Mana-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.88,0:20:20.77,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}I-Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.77,0:20:22.65,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Then I'll talk to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.65,0:20:23.99,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}I'll be right back.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.82,0:20:28.45,Yaku M,Man,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.45,0:20:32.42,Yaku M,Man,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Jun-chan told me that you saved me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.91,0:20:36.13,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}In truth, I didn't actually "save" you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.49,0:20:41.51,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}So, what kind of photographs were they?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.42,0:20:46.24,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}The photographs that caused the fight with your friends were pictures of Izumida-kun, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.24,0:20:50.91,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Your friends saw them and teased you about liking older men, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.91,0:20:52.91,Yaku M,Man,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}How can you tell?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.91,0:20:53.65,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Just tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.60,0:21:04.28,Yaku M,Man,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}I'll give that to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.66,0:21:06.94,Yaku M,Man,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}As appreciation for saving me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.94,0:21:09.24,Yaku M,Man,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}I don't want to be indebted to my rival.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.91,0:21:11.71,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Then I'll keep it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.18,0:21:29.37,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Is it really okay for me to not take her home?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.37,0:21:30.85,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}It's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.85,0:21:34.33,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}She's more mature than you think.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.81,0:21:38.16,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Besides, you have to take me home.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.21,0:21:41.63,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}It's already late, so you can stay at my place if you want to.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.63,0:21:45.59,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Are we going to marathon "Mystery, Thursday the Twelfth" until morning again?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.59,0:21:48.18,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Before we do, I'm tired, so you must give me a massage.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.18,0:21:50.96,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}That'll make me a manservant!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.96,0:21:52.07,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.07,0:21:53.79,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}It's an honorable job, unworthy of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.73,0:23:27.76,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Chizumiru Indajuu.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.76,0:23:29.21,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.21,0:23:31.14,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}I've rearranged your name, Izumida Jun'ichirou.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.14,0:23:32.26,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}And that would make me...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.26,0:23:34.01,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Yakushiji Ryoko's Supernatural Case File,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.01,0:23:35.43,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}File Number 06:
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.43,0:23:36.56,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Made in Kasumigaseki.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.56,0:23:37.68,Yaku M,Jun,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Please look forward to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.68,0:23:39.27,Yaku M,Ryo,0000,0000,0000,,{\be1\3a&H30&\fscx110}Jiryo Yakujiko...
